A drought, thought to be influenced by ocean temperature
abnormalities, hit 29% of the continental United States in 1988.
Grain production was probably 31% below the previous year.  The
results of the drought were not as bad as expected and the farmers
were saved by $3.9 billion in drought relief payments.</SUM>
